            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH8x4309-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.143" xml:lang="en" resp="#andrea.breard" modified="2023-12-28T03:11:07.086+09:00">Simplifying parts.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.144" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:35:02.974+09:00">Take the numerator away from the denominator;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.145" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:36:38.283+09:00">also take the denominator away from the numerator.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.146" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:36:45.398+09:00">When the values of the numerator and denominator are equal to one another,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.147" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:36:51.495+09:00">then simplify them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.148" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:40:36.215+09:00">Some say that</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.149" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:37:39.527+09:00">there is a procedure for simplifying parts which says:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.150" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:37:47.764+09:00">If one can halve, halve them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.151" xml:lang="en" resp="#andrea.breard" modified="2023-12-28T03:27:24.94+09:00">If they can be made to correspond to a single [value], [divide them by] that single corresponding [value].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.152" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:38:31.899+09:00">Another procedure for this says:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.153" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:38:57.038+09:00">Take the numerator away from the denominator.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.154" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:39:10.685+09:00">If it is the lesser take the denominator away from the numerator.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.155" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:39:21.203+09:00">When the numerator and denominator have become equal, take that [number] as the divisor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.156" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:39:30.135+09:00">For [each time] numerator and denominator accommodate the divisor, one unit is accomplished.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.157" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:39:40.528+09:00">If it is not worth taking away, but if [numerator and denominator] can be halved,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.158" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:40:14.099+09:00">halve the denominator, also halve the numerator.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.159" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:40:20.523+09:00">162/2016</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.160" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2022-12-14T20:40:28.171+09:00">simplifies to 9/112.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.545" xml:lang="en" resp="#andrea.breard" modified="2023-01-04T20:04:41.298+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.546" xml:lang="en" resp="#andrea.breard" modified="2023-01-04T20:04:35.683+09:00">Take what was bought or sold (i.e., volume/weight measured by the unit dan) as divisor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.545.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#andrea.breard" modified="2023-01-04T20:05:23.92+09:00">The procedure for calculating the unit [price] of each dan says:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH8x4309_CHANT_001-1a.143.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#andrea.breard" modified="2023-12-28T03:11:07.53+09:00">The procedure for simplifying parts says:</seg>
                </p>
